results.definition: a piece of open land for recreational use in an urban area
examples: they went for a walk in the park

results.definition: belonging to or participated in by a community as a whole; public
examples: common lands are set aside for use by all members of a community

results.definition: having no special distinction or quality; widely known or commonly encountered; average or ordinary or usual
examples: it is common knowledge that she lives alone

results.definition: common to or shared by two or more parties
examples: the mutual interests of management and labor

results.definition: being or characteristic of or appropriate to everyday language
examples: the vulgar tongue of the masses
the technical and vulgar names for an animal species

results.definition: of or associated with the great masses of people
examples: the common people in those days suffered greatly
behavior that branded him as common

results.definition: of low or inferior quality or value
examples: of what coarse metal ye are molded"- Shakespeare
produced...the common cloths used by the poorer population

results.definition: lacking refinement or cultivation or taste
examples: he had coarse manners but a first-rate mind
behavior that branded him as common
an untutored and uncouth human being
an uncouth soldier--a real tough guy
appealing to the vulgar taste for violence
the vulgar display of the newly rich
